Rating: 4
Delicious! However, I suggest oven-roasting the squash (this adds a richer flavor and you can also bake the entire squash and double the recipe). I baked mine at 350 degrees F for approximately 45 min. I also added a clove of freshly minced garlic to the (doubled) recipe and plenty of salt & pepper. It is a wonderful side dish to any meat/sausage/fish!

Rating: 4
I thought this was great, even with a few substitutions and a tweak or two. I didn't have fresh basil, so I used dried, and I don't care for a lot of oregano so I used herbs de provence instead. I used shaved parm and a diced medium tomato. After I scraped the squash, I drained it and squeezed it out with a paper towel - otherwise it would have been much too watery. We really loved this as a side-dish to roasted chicken.

