Following the reviews of the cooks that came before me, I baked the spaghetti squash in the oven at 375 for 40 minutes. I sauteed onion, sliced baby bella mushroom, and garlic in olive oil with the oregano and then added the basil and 1/2 lb of shrimp. I topped it with a shredded 3 cheese blend. This was my first experience with spaghetti squash, and I was very pleasantly surprised. I look forward to making this dish again.

Rating: 0
I didn't give this a fork rating as i changed so much of the recipe after reading the reviews. But I sauteed 2 cloves garlic in olive oil with one 1 tsp italian herbs and then added a can of drained tomatoes. Then I added 1/4 cup sun-dried tomatoes, a 1/2 cup black olives and a small jar of artichokes. I let it simmer for a bit and then poured all over the strings of spaghetti squash that i'd already baked in the oven for about 3/4 hour. (I had nestled the stringy squash into a lasagna pan.) I topped it with 1/2 cup grated fresh parmesean cheese and chopped fresh basil, then baked for about 20 minutes. Really great. My husband loved it and now prefers it to regular spaghetti. Also, I baked the squash teh night before and took out the insides, then stored in the refrigerator.

