Rating: 3
Following everyone's advice, I adapted the recipe as follows: Roasted the squash in the oven, at 375 for 45 minutes. Roasted, for the same time/temp 3 roma tomatoes, 2 orange tomatoes, 3 salad tomatoes, some fresh garlic, chopped sweet onion, basil, dried oregano, tons of olive oil, cracked pepper and sea salt. Garnished with fresh grated Parmesan-Reggiano. Unbelievable.

Rating: 4
Taking all of the prior reviewers' advice, I made the following changes with FABULOUS results: I roasted about 8 roma tomatoes, quartered, in plenty of good olive oil, with whole garlic cloves and fresh oregano-for about 2 hrs in a low oven. I added the tomatoes and their oil, to the cooked spaghetti squash. I then added the fresh basil, some toasted pine nuts and good parmesan. I then took it a step further and added some cooked chicken breast, which made for a very hearty fall meal. The tomatoes take a while, but they're pretty hands-off...well worth the time, if you have it.

