Rating: 3
Faced with a totally unfamiliar spaghetti squash and not a single recipe, I turned to save-the-day Epicurious and there it was. Many reviewers thought it was too bland, so I dug through my overflowing condiment shelf and came up with sun-dried tomatoes (I had no fresh ones on hand and I don't live in the city) and a jar of artichoke/caper spread. While the squash was steaming I minced only one garlic clove for this smaller-than-recipe squash and added it to the olive oil, chopped sun-dried tomatoes, artichoke spread, oregano and basil, with fresh-ground salt and pepper. Goo-oo-ood, oh my! I completely forgot the parmesan, which would have been perfect. My only advice is to use fresh herbs for sure-- the dried ones I had on hand were pretty blah, and the dish would sing with bright fresh basil and oregano. My squash was about 1-1/2 pounds, and 8 minutes in the MW was almost overdone. Definitely one to repeat!

